Nodar Kumaritashvili Nodar Kumaritashvili during a training run at the games in Whistler, Canada Georgian hopeful Nodar Kumaritashvili flew off the track and into a metal pole in Whistler, Canada. Medics administered CPR at the scene following the second of two training runs. Kumaritashvili was then placed on a stretcher with blood pouring from his head and taken away in an ambulance. An International Olympic Committee official confirmed tonight that the luger had died. Officials console each other Officials console each other as paramedics treat the badly injured luger Witnesses told how the 21-year-old crashed at one of the fastest points near the bottom of the track on the final 270-degree turn. He hit both sides of the wall before being hurled over the top and smashing into the pole at the side of the track Earlier Italian Armin Zoeggler, the 2002 and 2006 gold medalist, also crashed but was not badly injured. On Wednesday there were several accidents during women's luge training runs. Romania's Violeta Stramaturaru was knocked unconscious for a few minutes and taken to hospital. item.title: a conflict between Beijing Guoan n Pohang Steelers on a football ground
item.description:
a conflict between Beijing Guoan n Pohang Steelers on a football ground
white kit - Beijing Guoan (Chinese Super League Cup Holders) red kit - Pohang Steelers (AFC Champions League Cup Holders) the Barbarism of Beijing Guoan The Incident occured on 10th Feb. 2010 at Gumamoto, Japan. Pohang Steelers(KOR) went their to train for 2010 season cuz many east-asian football leagues including K-league start on spring(March) n finish on fall. u know, winter is too cold to play football for some areas n grounds r frozen. Steelers set a few training matches during the training period in Gumamoto with teams training at their like itself. Beijing Guoan(CHN) was the 4th opponent of Steelers' training matches. Beijing Guoan had been tough n rude during the match. even the chief refree of the match was so inexperienced that he couldn't control the dangerous situations. moreover, the match was supposed to b held at 14:00 but Beijing Guoan arrived at the stadium 1 hour late n it started at 14:45. n after 15minutes since the kick-off of 1st half, the refrees stopped the match for abt 20 minutes cuz the weather was too bad. so, the match had to b played among disordered atmosphere. when the 1st half was abt to end, one of Beijing Guoan got a red card for his tough plays. players of Pohang Steelers kept stony-hearted, and in 2nd half, Mota, a brazilian footballer of Pohang Steelers, fell off with one of Beijing Guoan after a conflict. Finally, Beijing Guoan comitted an outrage on the gound while the football match was going on. at that moment, other players n coaches suddenly rushed into the spot n started to attack the players. Though Pohang Steelers didnt answer for the violation of Beijing Guoan, whole the staffs n players of Beijing Guoan started to strike the players of Pohang Steelers with their fists, stepped n kicked the players even in their spiked football footwares. furthermore, one coach of Beijing Guoan handed a folded iron chair to hit the players of Pohang Steelers.(I guess the coach of Beijing Guoan prefered WWE rather than football matches n pretended that he was Triple H). refrees stopped the match in time. Mota was injured in the incident. this violation of Beijing Guoan, of course, should b blamed legalistically by an official case for their violations, but the worse is, this barbarism of Beijing Guoan is done on the football field during a sport called 'football'. the barbarism of Beijing Guoan is an absolute difiance to the sacred fair play spirit that always emphasized by FIFA and runs against the sportsmanship which is fundamental for all kinds of athletes. with the incident, it is hard to believe that players of Beijing Guoan r athletes. oh, wait a moment. i think i deceived myself. i m sure that they r athletes. they must b wrestlers or kickboxers, not footballers. they r athletes anyway. i m afraid that this rude club take part in AFC Champions League n we Pohang Steelers have the possibility to encounter Bejing Guoan in AFC Champions League. in addition, i cannot avoid being astonished at the fact that Beijing Guoan is the chmpions of Chinese Super League 2009. what the pride of Chinese football league Beijing Guoan is! huh? hey, u readers, if u r an opponent or a potential opponent of Beijing Guoan, i would like to say to b careful of ur body. they will kick ur body, not a ball, +Suwon Bluewings also had a training match with Beijing Guoan before the day, n many players got yellow n red cards in that match, too. so they said that it was difficult to stand normal match.
